  "text": "The CT scans used in this study are from the Danish Lung Cancer Screening Trial [CITATION_1] . A multi-detector CT scanner (Mx 8000 IDT 16 row scanner, Philips Medical Systems) was used to acquire CT scans at 120 kV/40 mAs at maximum inspiration breath hold and without cardiac gating. This protocol leads to an effective dose of around 1 mSv [CITATION_2] . The scans were reconstructed with a sharp kernel (Philips D), in-plane isotropic resolution of 0.78 × 0.78 mm, and 1-mm slice thickness. Participants were current or former smokers between 50 and 70 years of age. For this study, 742 participants were randomly selected, which were divided into three nonoverlapping sets (see supplementary Table S1 for clinical characteristics of the entire data):",
